cs.RO, cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL

This paper focuses on the design and implementation of an algorithm for turn-taking prediction in physical human-robot collaboration scenarios, specifically in the context of a Robotic Scrub Nurse (RSN) system in the operating room. This involves the use of multimodal communication cues and the ability to comprehend human actions and behaviors. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics), followed by cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as the paper discusses the importance of natural and fluent collaboration between humans and robots. The paper also involves the use of machine learning algorithms for prediction, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the use of natural language processing techniques for understanding human communication, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
